<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="347" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1089,1770]" pageId="0" pageNumber="347">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,1574,1597]" pageId="0" pageNumber="347">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The external appearance clearly distinguishes this species from the others described so far. 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" genus="Argyresthia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goedartella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="347">Argyresthia goedartella</emphasis>
(Linnaeus, 
<number box="[408,462,1609,1632]" pageId="0" pageNumber="347" value="1758.0">1758</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
is coloured similarly but its wings are more shiny and the bands always well-defined (uninterrupted) (
<figureCitation box="[328,389,1643,1666]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 4. 3" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1817,1839]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,194,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[152,1435,191,1795]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 4. 3. Argyresthia goedartella— external appearance; Kojszówka, 10 Aug 2000, Poland 4. Argyresthia pygmaeellaexternal appearance; Brzezinka, 23 Jun 2006, Poland" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244830/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="347">
Fig 
<number box="[374,389,1643,1666]" pageId="0" pageNumber="347" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Toll" box="[411,533,1643,1666]" pageId="0" pageNumber="347" refString="Toll, S. (1947) Beitrag zur Microlepidopterenfauna von Nordost-Persien. Zeitschrift des Wiener Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 32, 107 - 116 + plates 1 - 3." type="journal article" year="1947">
Toll (
<number box="[470,525,1643,1666]" pageId="0" pageNumber="347" value="1947.0">1947</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
noted that the signum of 
<taxonomicName box="[817,960,1643,1666]" class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" genus="Argyresthia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirabiella">
<emphasis box="[817,960,1643,1666]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="347">A. mirabiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Denis et Schiffermuller, 1775" authorityName="Denis et Schiffermuller" authorityYear="1775" class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" genus="Argyresthia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pygmaella">
<emphasis box="[1186,1328,1643,1666]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="347">A. pygmaella</emphasis>
(Denis et Schiffermüller, 
<number box="[319,373,1678,1701]" pageId="0" pageNumber="347" value="1775.0">1775</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[395,454,1678,1701]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 6. 5" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1612,1634]" captionTargetBox="[224,1370,186,1578]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[198,1384,161,1590]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 6. 5. Argyresthia mirabiella— female genitalia 6. Signum (lines next to figures all refer to 10 Μm): a — Argyresthia mirabiella, b — Argyresthia goedartella, gen. slide YPO 75 / 2014, c — Argyresthia pygmaeella, gen. slide YPO 76 / 2014." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244831/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="347">
Fig 
<number box="[440,454,1678,1701]" pageId="0" pageNumber="347" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
c) but this statement concerns only the middle portion. The rear portion of the signum of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" genus="Argyresthia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirabiella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="347">A. mirabiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is less sclerotized, visible only with Nomarski illumination at high magnification. The signum of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" genus="Argyresthia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goedartella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="347">A. goedartella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[288,351,1747,1770]" captionStart="FIGURES 5 – 6. 5" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1612,1634]" captionTargetBox="[224,1370,186,1578]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[198,1384,161,1590]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5 – 6. 5. Argyresthia mirabiella— female genitalia 6. Signum (lines next to figures all refer to 10 Μm): a — Argyresthia mirabiella, b — Argyresthia goedartella, gen. slide YPO 75 / 2014, c — Argyresthia pygmaeella, gen. slide YPO 76 / 2014." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244831/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="347">
Fig. 
<number box="[338,351,1747,1770]" pageId="0" pageNumber="347" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
b) is also very different from that of 
<taxonomicName box="[740,881,1747,1770]" class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" genus="Argyresthia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="347" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirabiella">
<emphasis box="[740,881,1747,1770]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="347">A. mirabiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
